{
  "texts": [
    "Given the rapid pace of development, governments and independent experts should refresh the Global Risk Index regularly-ideally every six months-to avoid strategic surprises.",
    "This process should be done in consultation with tool developers and funders, who can help identify emerging capabilities and improve assessment methods.",
    "Piloting AI-enabled automation could significantly improve the efficiency of these ongoing assessments.",
    "Governments should refresh the Global Risk Index regularly-ideally, every six months-partnering with external, independent biosecurity experts, where appropriate.",
    "Funders and developers should be consulted as they have a better view of emerging capabilities and can enhance assessment rubrics and rapidly identify new tools of interest."
  ]
}